@startuml
title Calculator — Class Diagram

class Calculator {
  +add(a, b) : float
  +subtract(a, b) : float
  +multiply(a, b) : float
  +divide(a, b) : float
  +power(base: float, exponent: float) : float
  +factorial(n: int) : int
  +square(x: float) : float
  +cube(x: float) : float
  +square_root(x: float) : float
  +cube_root(x: float) : float
  +log(x: float) : float
  +ln(x: float) : float
}

note right of Calculator
  Uses math.factorial, math.sqrt,
  math.cbrt, math.log10, math.log
end note

class InputLoop <<module>> {
  +OPERATIONS : dict
  +print_menu() : None
  +get_operation(input_fn: Callable) : str | None
  +get_operands(count: int, input_fn: Callable) : list[float]
  +dispatch(operation: str, operands: list, calc: Calculator) : float
  +run_loop(input_fn: Callable) : None
}

class Main <<module>> {
  +main() : None
}

class CLI <<module>> {
  +run_cli(argv: list[str] | None) : None
}

InputLoop --> Calculator : uses
Main --> InputLoop : calls run_loop()
Main --> CLI : calls run_cli()
CLI --> InputLoop : uses OPERATIONS, dispatch

@enduml
